OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1778652345
OL,3,CKeir Starmer to meet key rival Wes
OL,4,CStreeting amid open revolt in Labour
OL,5,CParty
OL,7,FThe Prime Minister has sought to push
OL,8,Fon, already having replaced four
OL,9,Fministers ` including prominent MP
OL,10,FJess Phillips and health minister
OL,11,FZubir Ahmed, an ally of Mr Streeting `
OL,12,Fwho quit the Government and called for
OL,13,FSir Keir to stand down.
OL,15,FIn Tuesday's Cabinet meeting, the
OL,16,FPrime Minister vowed to fight on, and
OL,17,Fwas publicly backed by several
OL,18,Fministers at the top of Government,
OL,19,Fincluding his deputy David Lammy, who
OL,20,Furged colleagues to "step back and
OL,21,Ftake a breath".
OL,26,@|D@UOU}D@NO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
